Pere Areny was the last man to be executed in [[Andorra]]. He was shot by a [[firing squad]] for the murder of his brother, Antoni Areny, on 18 October 1943.<ref>http://www.bondia.ad/societat/es-compleixen-70-anys-de-la-darrera-execucio-al-principat</ref> [[Capital punishment]] was abolished in Andorra in 1990<ref>{{cite web|title=1943: Antoni Areny, the last executed in Andorra|url=http://www.executedtoday.com/2014/10/18/1943-antoni-areny-the-last-executed-in-andorra/|website=ExecutedToday.com|accessdate=17 November 2016|date=18 October 2014}}</ref> and Protocol No. 6 to the [[ECHR]] came into force on 1 February 1996.

