'''''Share of throat''''' is a [[beverage industry]] term that refers to the proportion of the world's beverage consumption produced by a single company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.waywordradio.org/share_of_throat/|title=A Way with Words {{!}} share of throat|website=www.waywordradio.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-08}}</ref> The term was originally coined by [[Coca-Cola]] as "throat share",<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.economist.com/node/15772138|title=Taking the challenge|website=The Economist|language=en|access-date=2018-06-08}}</ref> in order to measure how much of the world's beverages were theirs, but is now more commonly referred to as ''share of throat''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.stltoday.com/business/columns/a-b-inbev-innovation-director-speaks-uses-term-d-art/article_976eae39-dfdc-5a83-b310-47bef606a482.html|title=A-B InBev innovation director speaks, uses term d'art "share of throat"|last=Frankel|first=Todd|work=stltoday.com|access-date=2018-06-08|language=en}}</ref>

